Subject: Re: [T2] 71 Westy Wiper Arm Removal question

Steve Dolan is right about the heat part.  Many times, i've used a normal 
household hair dryer to help get bolts, connections, etc. loose.  it's 
amazing how much help it is and it causes no damage.  Of course I only hold 
the heat to it for 15-30 seconds.  Greg

